Uses of Package
org.biohipi.imagebundle

  • Packages that use org.biohipi.imagebundle 
    Package Description
    org.biohipi.imagebundle
    Classes for storing and manipulating collections of images.
    org.biohipi.imagebundle.mapreduce
    Classes for processing BioHIBs including producing input splits and reading and decoding image records in the context of a MapReduce program.
  • Classes in org.biohipi.imagebundle used by org.biohipi.imagebundle 
    Class and Description
    BioHipiImageBundle
    A BioHipiImageBundle (BioHIB) is the primary representation for a collection of biomedical images on the Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) used by BioHIPI.
    BioHipiImageBundle.BioHibReader
    This FileReader enables reading individual images from a BioHipiImageBundle and delivers them in the specified image type.
  • Classes in org.biohipi.imagebundle used by org.biohipi.imagebundle.mapreduce
